Hard Q1 — SAP Purchase Order Analysis 80 rows
This is real SAP-style Purchase Order data from a manufacturing company. Paste it in Excel then answer all questions below using only formulas — no manual counting.

Write all answers in a Summary area below your data (row 85 onwards):

1. Total PO Amount across all orders: SUM
2. Average PO Amount per order: AVERAGE
3. Highest single PO Amount: MAX
4. Lowest single PO Amount: MIN
5. Total number of PO entries: COUNTA on PO ID column
6. Count of Delayed deliveries: COUNTIF on Delivery Status
7. Count of Pending deliveries: COUNTIF
8. Count of North region Delayed POs: COUNTIFS (region=North AND status=Delayed)
9. Count of West region Overdue payments: COUNTIFS (region=West AND payment=Overdue)
10. Total PO Amount for South region: SUMIF
11. Total PO Amount for Delivered + Paid orders: SUMIFS (delivery=Delivered AND payment=Paid)
12. Total PO Amount for East region Delayed orders: SUMIFS
13. Average PO Amount for North region: AVERAGEIF
14. Average PO Amount for Delivered orders only: AVERAGEIF
15. Average PO Amount for West region Pending orders: AVERAGEIFS
16. GST Tax column (col J): =ROUND(H2*18%,2) → drag down for all rows
17. Total with Tax column (col K): =H2+J2
18. Rounded Total column (col L): =ROUNDUP(K2,0)
19. Budget Variance column (col M) — Budget is fixed at 75000 per order: =ABS(H2-75000)
20. Count orders where PO Amount is above average: COUNTIF using AVERAGE result


